app.run()
Starts the application. Fires the init then ready lifecycle events.
app.run(): Promise&lt;void&gt;

app.lazy(loader)
Lazily imports a module. Returns a Promise that resolves to the module.
app.lazy(loader: () =&gt; Promise&lt;unknown&gt;): Promise&lt;unknown&gt;

Plugins are plain objects with a name and setup function. The setup function receives the app instance and can hook into any lifecycle event.
const myPlugin = {
  name: 'my-plugin',
  setup(app) {
    app.on('ready', () =&gt; {
      // plugin logic here
    })
  }
}

const app = create({ plugins: [myPlugin] })


Pass options to your plugin by wrapping it in a factory function:
const myPlugin = (options = {}) =&gt; ({
  name: 'my-plugin',
  setup(app) {
    console.log('options:', options)
  }
})

const app = create({ plugins: [myPlugin({ verbose: true })] })

